When requesting an individual deal by id, I get the expected data back. But when using the `batchAPI.read` endpoint, I get an error saying the deal doesn't exist. See request and response below. Is this a problem with the API or am I doing something wrong?

snippet from request:
```const BatchReadInputSimplePublicObjectId = { properties: ["amount","pipeline"], idProperty: "hs_object_id", inputs: [{"id":"7417136282"},{"id":"7417072295"}] };
const archived = false;

try {
  const apiResponse = await HubSpotClient.crm.deals.batchApi.read(BatchReadInputSimplePublicObjectId, archived);
  console.log(JSON.stringify(apiResponse.body, null, 2));
} catch (e) {
  e.message === 'HTTP request failed'
    ? console.error(JSON.stringify(e.response, null, 2))
    : console.error(e)
}```
